          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>On the surface of the medulla, the rootlets of the glossopharyngeal, vagus, and accessory nerves (CN IX, X, XI) emerge lateral to which structure?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Pyramid</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The pyramid lies anteriorly, flanking the anterior median fissure. The hypoglossal nerve (CN XII) exits between the pyramid and olive, but CN IX, X, and XI exit more laterally.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Olive</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct! The olive is the oval eminence overlying the inferior olivary nucleus on the anterolateral surface. CN IX, X, and XI rootlets emerge in a line just lateral to it.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Gracile tubercle</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The gracile tubercle is on the posterior surface of the lower closed medulla, overlying the nucleus gracilis. It is not an anterior landmark related to these cranial nerve exits.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Cuneate tubercle</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The cuneate tubercle is also on the posterior surface, lateral to the gracile tubercle. CN IX, X, and XI rootlets emerge from the anterolateral medulla, not the posterior surface.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "The olive is the correct landmark. Two exit zones to remember: CN XII rootlets exit between pyramid and olive, while CN IX, X, and XI rootlets exit lateral to the olive."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Well done. Remember the two key exit zones on the anterior medulla: CN XII between pyramid and olive, and CN IX, X, XI lateral to the olive."
                }
              ],
